With only one week to the start of national examinations, briefings for officials are going on countrywide and the Kenya National Examinations Council (Knec) is finalising logistics to distribute the examination materials to the counties. 

County and sub-county directors of education have been briefing centre managers (school heads) and supervisors who will, in turn, induct the invigilators. 



