The chair of Knec, John Onsati, said that although some cases of cheating were detected in the last examinations, the vice had been greatly minimised. 

During the briefing in Vihiga County on Wednesday, the county commissioner, Ochilo Oyugi, said that only centre managers will be allowed to use mobile phones during the examination period. Official says pregnant candidates in school, while the heavily pregnant or with complications are preparing for exams at home The outcome will be part of the final grade which will determine their transition from primary to junior secondary school. The President has also announced that funerals will take place within 72 hours. In just 12 months, the number of the dead has swelled – now heading towards 1,900 in Kenya. There was presidential level security in Nairobi Hospital’s VIP North Wing and access to the premier hospital’s presidential suites was more severe than usual.